ERROR:SPACING: space prohibited before that ',' (ctx:WxW)
#217: FILE: drivers/base/firmware_class.c:425:
+	fw_priv = kzalloc(sizeof(*fw_priv) + strlen(fw_name) + 1 , GFP_KERNEL);
 	                                                         ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:SPACING: No space is necessary after a cast
#230: FILE: drivers/base/firmware_class.c:436:
+		    firmware_class_timeout, (u_long) fw_priv);

WARNING:SPACING: space prohibited between function name and open parenthesis '('
#455: FILE: drivers/base/firmware_class.c:651:
+	fw_work = kzalloc(sizeof (struct firmware_work), gfp);

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*fw_work)...) over kzalloc(sizeof (struct firmware_work)...)
#455: FILE: drivers/base/firmware_class.c:651:
+	fw_work = kzalloc(sizeof (struct firmware_work), gfp);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

